rtscar Vintage Racing Association takes to the track in an event featuring Morgans, Triumphs, and Austin-Healeys. $40 weekend pass. (404) 298-3323. Nascar Nextel All-Star Challenge, Lowe’s Motor Speedway, Concord, N.C. $29-$88. nascar.com Silver Reno Showcase Auction, Reno/Sparks Convention Center, Reno, Nev. Admission fee. (800) 255-4485. Lake Placid Festival of Cars, Olympic Center, Lake Placid, N.Y. Cars, trucks, motorcycles, sport compacts — even boats. $15 weekend pass. (518) 523-2581. Saratoga Automobile Museum’s Spring Auto Show, Saratoga Springs, N.Y. Automobiles and motorcycles compete for prizes in two dozen categories. $8. (518) 587-1935. Mecum Belvidere High Performance Auction, Boone County Fairgrounds, Belvidere, Ill. The 20th anniversary of this muscle car auction. $10. (815) 568-8888. Newport Concours d’Élégance, Belle Mer, Newport, R.I. Road tours on Saturday and Sunday, concours on Monday. $20. (401) 767-7967. Indianapolis 500, Indianapolis Motor Speedway. $40-$150. Nascar Coca-Cola 600, Lowe’s Motor Speedway, Concord, N.C. $39-$135. nascar.com. Monaco Grand Prix, Monte Carlo. Sunday grandstand pass, $131-$751. formula1.com. Kruse Auburn Spring Motorfair, Auburn, Ind. In a town with a well-known automotive heritage, a thousand vehicles in an auction, swap meet and car corral at the Kruse Auction Park. $10. (800) 968-4444. National Street Rod Association Nationals East, York Expo Center, York, Pa. More than 4,200 pre-1949 hot rods, plus a vintage swap meet. $12. (901) 452-4030. Greenwich Concours d’Élégance, Roger Sherman Baldwin Park, Greenwich, Conn. Saturday’s concours is for American-made cars; Sunday’s is for imports. Christie’s will hold an auction on Sunday. $20 a day or $30 for both days. (203) 618-0460. The Original British Car Day, Lilypons Water Gardens, Adamstown, Md. This year marks the event’s 30th anniversary. $5 a car. (301) 831-5300. Nascar Dover 400, Dover International Speedway, Dover, Del. $50-$96. nascar.com Los Angeles Concours